en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-1992724765009579v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by kerem.tech", "description": "Python is the most widely used language in offensive security, not because it's trendy, but because it gives you full control over every layer of an attack or defense workflow.\n\nMost professional security tools you use daily are either built with Python or have a Python API. Learning these libraries doesn't just help you in CTFs, it makes you dangerous in real engagements.\n\nHere are 7 libraries every security engineer should have in their toolkit:\n\n1. Scapy: craft, send, and sniff raw network packets at any protocol layer. Used for recon, fuzzing, and building custom scanners.\n\n2. Impacket: interact with Windows protocols like SMB, MSRPC, and LDAP. Essential for credential dumping, Pass-the-Hash, and AD attacks.\n\n3. python-nmap: drive Nmap directly from your Python scripts. Automate port scanning and service enumeration in your own tooling.\n\n4. Paramiko: pure-Python SSH2 client. Automate remote command execution, file transfers, and port tunneling without shelling out.\n\n5. Shodan: query the internet's largest index of exposed devices via API. Find vulnerable systems without ever touching the target.\n\n6. pwntools: the go-to framework for CTF and binary exploitation. Simplifies buffer overflows, ROP chains, and shellcode generation.\n\n7. Cryptography: production-safe primitives for encryption, hashing, and key management. Use it whenever you need real crypto in your tools.\n\nSave this. Pick one library. Build something with it this week.\n\n#cybersecurity #python #ethicalhacking #redteam #infosec", "duration": 8.058, "timestamp": 1775038267, "uploader_id": "54638301196", "uploader": "Kerem 🛡 Cyber Security Engineer", "channel": "kerem.tech", "like_count": 4508, "comment_count": 69, "comments": [{"author": "dalla.admin", "author_id": "74679157232", "id": "18073362752293797", "text": "", "timestamp": 1778722021}, {"author": "dalla.admin", "author_id": "74679157232", "id": "17897515416449265", "text": "🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥👏👏👏👏", "timestamp": 1778721967}, {"author": "its_me_smart_rithish", "author_id": "70939336529", "id": "18113192194854104", "text": "🙌", "timestamp": 1778691477}, {"author": "pain_____arts", "author_id": "66268608413", "id": "17920063503358141", "text": "Cybersecurity & Cyber Professionals Community\nExclusive Discord server for cybersecurity experts, ethical hackers, and cyber enthusiasts. Connect, collaborate, and stay ahead of the latest security trends with fellow professionals.\nJoin: https://discord.gg/hZGddFdv6", "timestamp": 1778508746}, {"author": "plus_ultra_0007", "author_id": "58145558297", "id": "18113092960694313", "text": "🙌🙌", "timestamp": 1777462838}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://instagram.ftlv6-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t51.71878-15/661494478_1470853341119926_9051931703554740878_n.jpg?se=-1&stp=dst-jpegr_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42NDAuaGRyLnZpZGVvX2RlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJfZnJhbWUuYzIifQ&_nc_ht=instagram.ftlv6-1.fna.fbcdn.net&_nc_cat=110&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gEocuCbC9CDVpU4MiSafHDynLmU-x_-eegNz-zFb0FJk5JuvBW6yJGEuaMjB4V0ZK-HHU6TWAntTbTwsVWixTuM&_nc_ohc=S454W-jTK_MQ7kNvwE2brEN&_nc_gid=oz_wDE7bk1t64jfvXXZ5BA&edm=ANTKIIoBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_Af6ocG_dAQU-hQ_LTKLYrwSFxiCGNPoI3iMhgfWyXhKBVA&oe=6A110C54&_nc_sid=d885a2", "width": 640, "height": 1136, "id": "0", "resolution": "640x1136"}, {"url": "https://instagram.ftlv6-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t51.71878-15/661494478_1470853341119926_9051931703554740878_n.jpg?se=-1&stp=dst-jpegr_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42NDAuaGRyLnZpZGVvX2RlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJfZnJhbWUuYzIifQ&_nc_ht=instagram.ftlv6-1.fna.fbcdn.net&_nc_cat=110&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gEocuCbC9CDVpU4MiSafHDynLmU-x_-eegNz-zFb0FJk5JuvBW6yJGEuaMjB4V0ZK-HHU6TWAntTbTwsVWixTuM&_nc_ohc=S454W-jTK_MQ7kNvwE2brEN&_nc_gid=oz_wDE7bk1t64jfvXXZ5BA&edm=ANTKIIoBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_Af6ocG_dAQU-hQ_LTKLYrwSFxiCGNPoI3iMhgfWyXhKBVA